cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about conditional image generation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a deep learning model for image generation, which falls under the subfield of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of disentangled representations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also mentions fine-grained image generation tasks, which is a subfield of graphics, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses text-to-image generation, which is a subfield of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
